race.comment: RESET THE JAZZ (3) didn't threaten when resuming last start over 1600m at Flemington, finishing fifth, beaten 3 lengths. Second up record is very strong and getting within 3.15 lengths of Sabaj - a super-impressive winner of the Cranbourne Cup last weekend - last time looks great form for this. JUGIONG (11), who is eligible for, and has been contesting, easier races than this but is locally-trained and carries colours that have graced the winner's stall in this race before. There has been merit in recent runs and you get the feeling this has been a target race. HIYAAM PROUD (9) wasn't disgraced in city class last time when finishing seventh at Caulfield. Will find this much easier. Capable of testing this field. DARK JOURNEY (6) turned in a much better effort last time out to score by 0.8 lengths over 1620m at Donald. Solid top-three prospects. RHINOCEROS (1) is a Country Cups regular who has been struggling for his best form this time in but should be a peak fitness now.
